sentence.text: Purpose To determine whether the rates and tumor characteristics of screening-detected and interval cancers differ for two-dimensional digital mammography (DM) versus digital breast tomosynthesis (biological_process) mammography.

There were no significant differences in tumor characteristics, including size at pathologic examination, grade, hormone receptor status, and positive regulation of cysteine-type endopeptidase activity involved in apoptotic process status, between the screening-detected invasive cancers on DM versus biological_process (P = .09-.99).
